we have an application that was written using visual studio for mac.  it was working well and it ironically was one of the more stable applications we have.

recently, our macs and versions of visual studio where upgraded for macOS (mojave).


a minor edit to the app had to be done.  however the app no longer runs.  the simplest request calls no longer work.  they time out.  i run the same request in fiddler (pc) and charles (mac) and it works fine.  the data (json) is coming back.  however, for some reason, our app fails for the most basic get requests.    please help.

i know the immediate answer will be "upgrade"....but i'm hoping there is some other solution.

macOS version:  10.14
visual studio for mac:  7.6.9 (build 22)
restsharp dll version:  105.2.3.0

```csharp
var request = new RestRequest(@"checklist/listbyid?Id=" + someId, Method.GET);
request.RequestFormat = DataFormat.Json;
var response = ExecuteTaskAsync(request);
return response.Result.Content;


protected Task<IRestResponse> ExecuteTaskAsync(RestRequest request)
{
	
SetRequestHeaders (request);

var tcs = new TaskCompletionSource<IRestResponse>();
this.ExecuteAsync(request, (response) =>
	{
		if (response.ErrorException != null)
		{
			//tcs.TrySetException(response.ErrorException);
		    tcs.TrySetResult(response);
		}
		else
		{
			// handle user token's expiration when making service request
		if (response.StatusCode == HttpStatusCode.Unauthorized)
			{
				var messenger = Mvx.Resolve<IMvxMessenger>();
				if (messenger == null) return;
				messenger.Publish(new TokenExpireMessage(response));
			}

			tcs.TrySetResult(response);
		}
});
return tcs.Task;
}
```

